{"ts": "2026-06-08T01:43:47.356846+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 67b71353e546627b26b6ca6486602d2a9df9b881)", "id": "lc_9a730c1b-b409-4d26-9e6a-c9c7bb0ab5f9"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Versioned Documentation Site\n\nA Docusaurus site that keeps current and versioned documentation aligned across releases.\n\n## Project layout\n\n- `docs/` — Current documentation pages.\n- `versioned_docs/` — Version-specific documentation snapshots.\n- `versions.json` — Published documentation versions.\n- `sidebars.js` — Navigation for current docs.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n## Documentation workflow\n\n1. Add or update Markdown pages under `docs/`.\n2. Keep `sidebars.js` synchronized with new pages.\n3. Validate JavaScript config before opening a PR.\n4. Run a full Docusaurus build before release.\n\n## Maintenance notes\n\nKeep release notes and version links consistent across current and versioned docs.\n\n## Contributing\n\nKeep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.\n", "id": "lc_0a84fb9c-3774-468c-b0b2-57ae7676292c"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "53e05260-867a-4008-8ee6-bf466ac95765", "tool_call_id": "call_00_og33u32MRrqVWCNwJ1N75910", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T01:43:47.388458+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 37cec09afd9be614db8506b1d830fe91c6d843ac)", "id": "lc_6aabfe49-b50d-48e9-befe-1bb2a826d038"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Security Policy\n\n## Supported use\n\nVersioned Documentation Site is intended for local development, documentation maintenance, and controlled review workflows.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis repository contains documentation sources only. Do not include credentials, production tokens, or private customer data in documentation examples.\n\n## Reporting\n\nOpen a security issue through the project maintainer channel with reproduction steps and the affected files. Avoid posting secrets or sensitive environment details in public comments.\n", "id": "lc_1f709a51-a5f8-45cc-bc30-82bb25e47d82"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b1d7304e-d621-4a11-9914-79305700b48c", "tool_call_id": "call_01_nQckLwP0Sb8S6TyvrETx8277", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
